Responsibilities
Acts as HR business partner to support multi-brands organization and people needs. 
1.	Participate in key organization and people decisions and provide organizational diagnosis and human resources support in workforce planning, manager above level recruitment, training &amp; development, performance appraisal, incentive design and etc. to enable the implementation of business strategy;
2.	Identify critical talent gaps, drive and influence key talent actions on talent development, engagement and retention. Lead talent discussion based on clear understanding of business strategy, talent management concepts and also propose suitable actions;
3.	Build a mechanisms through day to day communication, and be cautious in knowing how company policies, changes , initiatives are working effectively or not;
4.	Work as internal consultant to address people issue to foresee potential problems may occurred and share with business leaders to find solution;
5.	Handle critical ER cases independently as per business needs. 

Requirements:
1.	Bachelor degree or above, 10+ years working experiences in organizational development/recruitment /performance management/employee relations and etc. with multi-business stakeholders supporting experiences.
2.	5 years of experiences as HRBP / HRM in Retail or Luxury or FMCG industries is preferred;
3.	Have a strong business understanding and thinking, can quickly understand the business and respond to the demands;
4.	Have the ability to find and solve problems in time, be flexible and proactive in providing solutions;
5.	Experiences in cross-functional collaboration and engagement with a focus on delivering exceptional support;
6.	Excellent communication and coordination ability, continuously learning and self-improvement.
7.	Fluent in oral and written English.

